name: Test -> load module series diode,
description: Temporarily bypass the series protection diode in the load module by placing a jumper wire directly across its anode and cathode terminals, then power the system and observe whether the main lamp and internal indicator lamp illuminate steadily. Remove the jumper immediately after the observation., outcome='The main load lamp is not lit.  \nThe internal indicator lamp, which is in parallel with the main load, is also not lit.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('short_ports', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> ambient sensor module potentiometer / wiring area,
description: Visually inspect the ambient sensor module around the timing and sensitivity potentiometers and their associated wiring/traces for any signs of intermittent shorting or miswiring—specifically look for a wiper terminal or track accidentally tied to the main +12 V line feeding the output, or any other unintended low‑resistance path that could be pulling the load‑module input up to about 0.3–0.4 V instead of 12 V., outcome='The sensitivity and timing potentiometers, as well as the sensor bias resistor, show no observable internal faults on visual inspection. The Control Output Cable (+) and Control Output Cable (−) both appear intact with no observable internal faults, and their external (port_n) connections are present; no polarity inversion is indicated in the observed cabling. No unintended shorts or miswiring to the +12 V line were visually identified in this inspection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=55.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> battery / power supply module source voltage under load,
description: Measure the DC voltage directly across the battery terminals inside the power supply module, and then across the external + and − output terminals of the power supply, while the system is powered and the relay is closed. Verify whether the source is actually around 12 V or is only about 0.36–0.4 V under load., outcome='The internal battery measures a normal 12.0 V across its terminals.  \nThe external PSU Output Cable (+) is at about 11.99 V, and the PSU Output Cable (−) is at about 0 V, so the supply is providing approximately 12 V at its external terminals under load.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module output + node relative to its own input + node,
description: With the system powered, place the voltmeter negative probe on the control module input − terminal. Measure the DC voltage at the control module input + terminal, then at the relay common node, and finally at the control module output + terminal (the internal node just before the external Control Output Cable (+) jack). Confirm whether 12 V is present at the relay common and whether there is any significant voltage drop between the module’s input + and the relay common, and between the relay common and the output + node., outcome='Measured DC voltage at the Control Input Cable (+) is ~11.99 V, and the relay common node also shows ~11.99 V, indicating no significant drop between input + and relay common.  \nThe Control Output Cable (+) node measures ~0.36 V, indicating a significant voltage drop between the relay common and the output + node.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module internal path between relay common node and Control Output Cable (+) node,
description: With power off, disconnect the Control Output Cable (+) and (−) from the load module so the control module output is completely unloaded. Then, with an ohmmeter referenced to the control module input − node, measure resistance from the relay common node to the Control Output Cable (+) node, and also from the Control Output Cable (+) node to the Control Output Cable (−) / input − node. Then power the system with the output still unloaded and measure DC voltage at the Control Output Cable (+) node relative to the input − node. Determine whether the output + node is being heavily loaded to ground or is only weakly connected to the relay common (high series resistance or unintended element)., outcome='The control relay and both Control Output Cables (+) and (−) show nominal low resistance/continuity values. With the output unloaded and referenced to the input − node, the Control Output Cable (+) measures 0.3592 V DC. No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED in the measured cabling.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=80.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module Control Output Cable (+) isolation from upstream +12 V path,
description: With power OFF, completely disconnect the Control Input Cable (+) from the power‑supply module so that the ambient sensor module has no +12 V applied at its input. Leave the Control Output Cable (+) and (−) disconnected from the load module as in the last test. Now, using the ohmmeter referenced to the control module input − node, measure the DC resistance from the (now-floating) Control Output Cable (+) node to the Control Input Cable (+) pad/traces inside the control module, and also from Control Output Cable (+) to the control module’s local ground / Control Output Cable (−) node. Report the resistances; this determines whether the ~0.36 V seen at the output is due to an internal active element that self-biases from elsewhere in the circuit rather than from the main +12 V path., outcome='Control Output Cable (+), Control Input Cable (+), and Control Output Cable (−) each show nominal continuity at approximately 0.10 Ω. No additional resistance measurements between Control Output (+) and the control module internal nodes were reported in these steps.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=60.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
